```json
{
  "application": "NAMD",
  "software_requirements": [
    "GCC/7.3.0-2.30",
    "OpenMPI/3.1.1",
    "NAMD/2.13-mpi"
  ],
  "resource_requirements": {
    "time": "00:50:00",
    "nodes": 1,
    "processes": 28
  },
  "output_files": [
    "job_o.out",
    "job_o.err",
    "logfile.txt"
  ],
  "input_file": "4ake_eq.conf"
}
```

The script runs the molecular dynamics simulation program **NAMD**. It uses the **GCC** compiler version 7.3.0-2.30, the **OpenMPI** library version 3.1.1, and the **NAMD** program version 2.13-mpi. It requires 1 node with 28 processes and runs for 50 minutes. It outputs results to three files: "job_o.out", "job_o.err", and "logfile.txt", and uses the "4ake_eq.conf" file as input.
